-- Egyptian Stocks: El Nasr Clothes and Beltone Financial Holding
-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a   a n d   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 2011-12-27T14:21:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-27/egyptian-stocks-el-nasr-clothes-and-maridive-oil-services.html
Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30)  fell
0.4 percent to 3,619.72 at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo, the
lowest level since Dec. 22. The measure has dropped 49 percent
this year, the third-worst performer among the world’s stock
markets tracked by Bloomberg.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.  El Nasr Clothes & Textiles (KABO)   retreated 1.7 percent
to 58 piasters, the lowest level since Dec. 22. The Cairo-based
clothing manufacturer also known as Kabo said its third-quarter
loss widened to 5.65 million Egyptian pounds ($937,600) from
1.25 million pounds a year earlier.  Beltone Financial Holding  (BTFH EY) climbed 3.7 percent to
12.87 pounds, the highest level since Nov. 30. Chief Executive
Officer Aladdin Saba said today he is in talks to sell his stake
in the Egyptian investment bank.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
